ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa will speak about this weekend's much-talked-about NEC meeting. The discussion has been characterised by audio leaks, which the ANC's legal team is investigating.   * Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa will speak about this weekend's heated National Executive Committee meeting.
The discussion has been characterised by audio leaks which the ANC's legal team is investigating. READ: ANC NEC members warn of party's collapse This, as two factions within the ruling party continue to battle for power. The NEC meeting was called to discuss the next steps with regard to the controversial step aside rule. Suspended Secretary-General Ace Magashule and ANC MP Bongani Bongo were kicked out of the virtual meeting on Saturday. READ: Mashele: Senior ANC members using party for own gain Magashule insists he remains the party's secretary-general because he is appealing his suspension. Political analyst Oliver Dickson says the party is extremely divided and is on the verge of collapse.